description:
Hi, my name is Álvaro, a software developer with a passion for solving problems by contributing to the order, action, and growth of the teams I work with. With a solid technical foundation and unique skill set, I strive to achieve desired results and foster a collaborative and comfortable environment where everyone can thrive.

I enjoy seeing the big picture and charting the most effective paths to solving a problem. I can abstract the scenarios well and connect the necessary dots, allowing me to learn, adapt, and achieve tangible results. This is quite useful in cost reduction tasks, where I have already been able to reduce MWAA log storage costs in CloudWatch on AWS by over 95% in one of my professional experiences.

Knowledge of the data pipeline and making data-driven decisions is one of the most important skills for today. Developing the entire pipeline, from collecting the raw data, processing it, and storing it until it serves as input for a decision-making process. One example was building a dashboard about coronavirus in the state of Rio Grande do Norte in Brazil, which helped local authorities in decision-making during the covid-19 pandemic.

I have worked in different business contexts, which made me adaptable to the proposed problem. I always value essential skills for context-independent software development, such as best practices, documentation, and negotiation strategies.

I believe that a relaxed and friendly environment makes people feel comfortable to express themselves. By promoting assertive communication and breaking the ice a bit, I try to bring out the best in people and contribute to a positive culture on the team, driving collaboration among all.

One of the things I enjoy most is the software development communities and contributing to free and open-source software. Every year I participate in Hacktoberfest hosted by GitHub, own and maintain software packages and libraries (mine and others), and participate in community events (as a participant, speaker, or organizer).

If you are looking for a professional who thinks outside the box, collaborates with peers, and has solid technical knowledge, let's connect! I'm always up for a conversation about exciting projects and opportunities.

Throughout my career, I have consistently delivered highly scalable web applications that surpass client expectations.

I possess a comprehensive understanding of the entire Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC), from requirements gathering and analysis to design, development, testing, and implementation. I am well-versed in popular SDLC methodologies such as Agile/Scrum, Waterfall, Test Driven Development (TDD), and Iterative Development. This allows me to adapt to different project requirements and deliver results efficiently.

One of my strengths lies in my extensive experience with various UI widgets using JavaScript and Angular-based libraries like jQuery. I have successfully implemented GDPR compliance systems across multiple applications, demonstrating my proficiency in ensuring data privacy and security.

In addition to my technical skills, I excel in interpersonal abilities, communication, time management, and teamwork. I thrive in high-pressure environments and work diligently to meet project deadlines. Throughout my years of leading projects, I have developed a range of skills, including project planning, team management, and problem-solving, all of which contribute to delivering high-quality results and ensuring client satisfaction.

As a Lead, I have honed my proficiency in implementing Agile methodologies effectively. I understand the importance of collaboration, iterative development, and continuous improvement in delivering successful software projects.

My core competencies include Angular, Cordova/Capacitor, JavaScript, Git/Git Bash/Smart Git, Node.js, Next.js, project management, Ionic, Bootstrap, Scrum Master/Agile, Amazon Web Services (AWS), HTML5/CSS3/SASS, TypeScript, and mobile app deployments/push notifications. With these skills and experiences, I am well-equipped to tackle diverse projects and deliver outstanding results.

In summary, I am a highly skilled and adaptable Software Developer with expertise in web design, user interface development, and the complete SDLC. My technical proficiency, project leadership abilities, and commitment to excellence make me a valuable asset for any development team or project.

training, mentoring and leading the team.

description:
I am an experienced iOS developer with a passion for video games. Over the past 10 years, I have built a solid reputation for developing high-quality and intuitive iOS applications that delight users. With a strong background in Swift and Objective-C, I have a proven track record of successfully designing and implementing complex features and functionalities for a wide range of iOS applications.

Throughout my career, I have worked on numerous projects ranging from gaming and entertainment to social media and e-commerce. My ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams has enabled me to deliver top-notch products that meet business and user needs. My strong problem-solving skills have allowed me to quickly identify and resolve issues, resulting in faster development cycles and higher quality products.

I have a deep understanding of the iOS ecosystem, including the latest frameworks, libraries, and tools. I am always up-to-date with the latest trends and best practices in the iOS development world, which allows me to provide valuable insights to stakeholders and contribute to the overall success of projects.

My passion for video games has inspired me to develop some of the most innovative and engaging gaming experiences on the App Store. My deep knowledge of game mechanics, graphics programming, and user engagement has allowed me to create immersive and captivating gaming experiences that keep users coming back for more.

Overall, I am an confident iOS developer with a passion for video games. With 10 years of experience under my belt, I have a wealth of knowledge and expertise that I bring to every project. Whether it's developing new features, optimizing performance, or resolving issues, I am committed to delivering high-quality products that exceed expectations.

description:
As an Artificial Intelligence Engineer and Team Leader at AViSTO, I have been responsible for building a software platform for vision-based Level Five highway and urban self-driving vehicles. With over four years of experience in this role, I have utilized the reinforcement learning algorithm and proximal policy optimization in a multi-agent environment with a reward function based on completing tasks. I developed a decaying structure combining simulated annealing with a random restart to exploit the exploration-exploitation tradeoff.

I have designed, developed, and implemented data science and machine learning models in proofs-of-concept and prototypes. My expertise in sensor selection and fusion for accurate localization using the Error-State extended Kalman filter has been crucial to the success of our platform. Also, I have developed a predictive maintenance solution for Schnieder SAS Industrial PLC and managed the scrum process from initiation to delivery. I also worked as a Data Engineer at Ozwillo and a Research and Development Engineer at Télécom SudParis, where I focused on developing expressive non-monotonic logic-based formalisms for the reasoning over uncertain data streams through logical constraints.

I am passionate about solving complex problems using AI and data science and look forward to continuing to innovate and lead in this field.

description:
I am presently employed as a ADAS MBD Verification and Validation, Scrum Master and MIL Expert in Renault Nissan Technology and Business Centre, where I have gained a reputation not only for my impressive work rate and integrity but also for my both technical and non-technical skills. The attached resume will provide a more complete overview of my accomplishments. However, what it may not show is that I am a self-motivated individual, who is able to perform well under pressure & who can bring to the table solid capabilities.
With reference to the qualifications described in the advertisement, you will see from the enclosed resume that I have:
• Coach Teams on how to integrate Agile values and principles.
• Assigning the tasks, handling the team members, and project the task status to management in the daily scrum. Handling discussion and resolution.
• Facilitate and establish a rhythm of touch points by ensuring full team engagement in Agile ceramics (e.g., Retrospective, Daily Scrum, Sprint Review, Sprint Planning and Refining).
• Performed PoC (Proof of Concept) for MIL validation which brought validation business to team.
• MIL (Model-In-Loop) validation is performed for the following ADAS (Advanced Driver Assistance System) features such as Distance warning, AD1 Enhancement, Automatic Parking etc. to ensure the functionality of the developed model meets the expectation of the requirements in the system perspective using Time Partition Testing (TPT) for Renault cars.
• SCA (Static Code Analysis) for ADAS to follow ISO26262 process (MISRA compliance and run time check using Polyspace code Prover)
• Performed unit level validation for Advanced Emergency Braking to check the functionality in the unit level and find the actual bug of the model using testcases of 100% coverage written in TPT.
• Created Test Vectors to achieve 100% requirement coverage and worked in model coverage improvement (MC-DC)
• Created testcases in MATLAB SLDV. Created testcases in Reactis for testing purposes. Code Generation Knowledge.
• Static Code Analysis (SCA), a requirement to ensure the application software is compliant with ISO26262 standards. This is mainly achieved by ensuring the auto code generated from Simulink model obeys MISRA rules and is free from any runtime errors.
• Performed Unit level validation for Advanced Emergency Braking to check the functionality in the unit level and find the actual bug of the model using testcases of 100% coverage written in TPT.

description:
I am Alkesh Ghorpade, a Staff Software Engineer with over 11 years of experience in the field. I am excited to apply for the Software Engineer position at your company that I recently came across, as it perfectly aligns with my professional goals.

With over 9 years of experience in Ruby on Rails and 1.5 to 2 years of experience in Golang and Java, I have worked on diverse projects and developed a strong foundation in web application development. I am a Ruby on Rails consultant at ShakaCode LLC. I am also working on a side project that involves automating blog posts on various platforms, including Medium, Dev.to, and Hashnode. You can find the repository link for the project here: http://github.com/alkesh26/automate-blog-posts.

I am a passionate open-source contributor and have contributed to projects such as Rails: https://contributors.rubyonrails.org/contributors/alkesh-ghorpade/commits, Go: https://go-review.googlesource.com/q/alkesh26, and the AWS SDK gem: https://github.com/aws/aws-sdk-ruby/pulls?q=is%3Apr+author%3Aalkesh26+is%3Aclosed. I also enjoy solving Data Structures and Algorithm problems and am active on coding platforms like LeetCode, InterviewBit, and HackerEarth. Furthermore, I have shared my knowledge and experience with others by blogging about Ruby on Rails while working with Saeloun: https://blog.saeloun.com/authors/alkesh, and I continue to write programming blogs which can be found at my personal blog here: http://alkeshghorpade.me.

description:
Good Day, 

I’m a Fullstack Developer with experience in front-end, back-end and mobile app development. Over my career, I’ve worked extensively with a range of technologies and languages including PHP, Python, C# and different accompanying frameworks like .Net, Laravel, ExpressJS, Django and more. 

At my previous positions, I’ve led small teams of developers. I’ve been directly responsible for application code (front and back), mentoring, training, quality assurance, code review, CI/CD pipelines and application deployment. 

I started my journey as a software developer working as an estimator in the construction industry over 15 years ago. I began by building applications using Excel and VBA to improve the estimating process and eventually progressed  into building user-interfaces to facilitate collaboration and communication between the sales and construction teams. 

During this time I discovered a real passion for building applications that drastically improved the processes and profits of the company I worked for. Since developing my first humble applications with Excel and VBA, I dedicated myself to programming and web-development starting with PHP, MySQL, HTML, CSS and Javascript. 

From my first foray into programming over a decade ago up to today, I’ve had the opportunity to build applications for a variety of industries including CRM’s for the financing industry, membership sites for professional organisations, custom e-commerce solutions, mobile applications, social media platforms and SaaS applications.

I’m an avid learner and have a strong passion for programming and application development. My goal is to find a position within your company where I can continue to expand upon my skills while becoming an integral and valuable part of your team!

Thank you for your time and consideration.

description:
I am a highly skilled software engineer with a diverse range of experiences in various technologies. With a strong focus on backend development, I have honed my expertise in building services and APIs using Golang. I am passionate about leveraging the power of Golang to create efficient, scalable, and high-performance applications that meet the needs of users and businesses alike.

In addition to Golang, I have a solid background in Python and the Django REST Framework. I have successfully developed APIs using these technologies, showcasing my ability to design and implement secure and feature-rich web services. I take pride in writing comprehensive unit tests, ensuring the reliability and quality of the code I produce, and contributing to the success of the projects I work on.

Frontend development is another area where I excel. I am proficient in React JavaScript and TypeScript, allowing me to create visually appealing and user-friendly interfaces. I enjoy the challenge of seamlessly integrating frontend systems with backend functionality, delivering dynamic and responsive web pages and screens.

Database management is a skill I have developed through extensive work with PostgreSQL. I possess a deep understanding of data modeling and storage optimization, utilizing PostgreSQL's advanced features to ensure optimal performance and data integrity in the applications I build.

I strongly believe in the power of automation and streamlined development processes. As a result, I have a solid grasp of continuous integration and continuous deployment (CI/CD) practices. I can set up efficient pipelines that facilitate seamless software deployment, enabling faster iteration and delivery of applications.

Version control is second nature to me, with expertise in Git and GitLab. I am skilled in managing code repositories, branching, merging, and resolving conflicts, ensuring smooth collaboration and versioning control within development teams.

My technical expertise extends to Linux tools and utilities, and I am comfortable working in a Linux environment. I leverage the command line interface and various Linux-based tools to optimize my workflow and troubleshoot technical issues effectively.

With my diverse skill set and adaptability to new technologies, I consistently deliver high-quality software solutions. My passion for innovation and dedication to excellence make me a valuable asset to any development team or organization I join. I thrive in collaborative environments, where I can contribute my skills and knowledge to create impactful solutions that drive success.

description:
I am a 2019 Computer Science graduate from the esteemed Indian Institute of Technology, BHU Varanasi (IIT BHU Varanasi). I gained admission to the institute by successfully clearing the highly competitive IIT-JEE exam, achieving a remarkable 99.94 percentile among 1.4 million applicants. With over 3.8 years of professional experience, I have been working at Amazon for more than 2.8 years.

During my tenure at Amazon, I had the opportunity to contribute to the Exports and Expansion Tax team. In this role, I was responsible for handling backend operations related to Tax Invoicing, supporting the launch of Amazon and its new features across various marketplaces.

Notably, I led the design and implementation of Amazon's first-ever dual currency Invoicing feature for the UAE-KSA Global Store Arc. This innovative solution allowed customers to conduct transactions using two different currencies seamlessly. Additionally, I successfully designed and implemented a multi-language Invoice generation feature, catering to Amazon customers who required their invoices in multiple Languages of Preferences (LOP).

Furthermore, I took charge of leading a team in launching the Tax Invoicing feature for key markets such as amazon.se, amazon.pl, amazon.eg, and amazon.sa prime.

These experiences have allowed me to develop a strong skill set in backend operations, design, and implementation, as well as project management.

Thank you for considering my application, and I look forward to the opportunity to discuss my qualifications in more detail.

I am a proactive individual who thrives in collaborative environments, leveraging my expertise to drive innovation and achieve tangible results. With a dedication to delivering high-quality software solutions, I am constantly seeking new challenges and opportunities for growth.

description:
Greetings, my name is Elton Alcantara, and I'm a seasoned Web Tech Lead with a demonstrated history of providing exceptional services in the technology sector. My recent tenure as the Web Tech Lead for QuikTrip, an innovative digital platform specializing in emissions reporting through real-time data and predictive analytics, showcases my ability to deliver outstanding results in a challenging environment.
As a frontend-focused full-stack engineer with over a decade of experience in web development, I've honed my skills in assisting both startups and established enterprises in conceptualizing and creating cutting-edge technologies. My expertise in brainstorming and prototyping sets me apart in the industry, enabling me to effectively collaborate with management, stakeholders, and C-level executives to ensure the delivery of top-notch performance and functionality.
My educational background includes a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science from Sao Paulo University, and I'm currently volunteering as a web developer for Doodles Academy. This diverse experience has allowed me to develop a deep understanding of various JavaScript and TypeScript frameworks such as React, Next, Gatsby, CMS and Node, as well as cloud services like AWS and Azure.
I firmly believe that my unique blend of skills, experience, and dedication make me an ideal candidate for any frontend engineering position. I'm eager to further discuss my qualifications and explore how my expertise can contribute to your organization's success.

I adap my schedule to the team's needs, excelling in communication whether via Zoom calls or direct messages, and I adhere to a disciplined home office routine to maintain productivity.

As a registered self-employed professional, I can operate as a contractor. This means I bill for my time and handle my own taxes, which I find mitigates many of the issues associated with hiring remote workers from another country.

My requirements are straightforward: fair compensation and ample paid time off.

Designed the whole load balancing approach for the module, making an ACTIVE-ACTIVE (HighAvailability) in different data center. This helped the bank in decomissioning vendor product and saved considerable amount in license cost.

Upgraded myself by making to machine learning concepts and have formal education in that field.
